By Vanessa Obioha The Recording Academy has announced Yemi Alade as part of the talents who will be unveiling the nominees for 2021 Grammys. In a statement, the company disclosed that the ‘Johnny’ crooner will be joining the Chair and Interim Recording Academy President/CEO Harvey Mason Jr. to announce the nominees on Tuesday, November 24. Other international celebrities lined up for the nomination announcement which will be live-streamed include four-time Grammy award-winning regional Mexican singer-songwriter Pepe Aguilar, CBS ‘This Morning’ anchor Gayle King, two-time Grammy award-winning singer Dua Lipa among others. The 63rd Grammys is slated for January 31, 2021.